The paper discusses a technique for citation analysis of documents retrieved from the Medline database using Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) at the Web of Knowledge and the Science Citation Index at the Web of Science. This technique can be applied to various fields of research, including computer science. The paper does not focus on a specific sub-category of computer science, but the use of citation analysis and indexing techniques suggests that it may be relevant to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
